<title>USA: World Bank appoints Stiglitz as chief economist.</title>
<headline>World Bank appoints Stiglitz as chief economist.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-12-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The World Bank on Wednesday named Joseph Stiglitz, outgoing chairman of President Clinton's Council of Economic Advisors, as its chief economist.</p>
<p>Stiglitz will take up his new post as Senior Vice President, Development Economics, and Chief Economist, on February 1, the bank said in a statement.</p>
<p>He will replace Michael Bruno, who left the World Bank at at the end of last month to return to his native Israel.</p>
